
Practical no 4

Aim:SSH server 

What is ssh server?

1)SSH stand for secure shell.

2)ssh is mainly used for securely logged into 

another device with remotely.

3)ssh uses for Data transfer from one machine to others 

Machine with securely.

Commands:

To install SSH, first update the package repository cache with

  sudo apt-get update

1)To install the OpenSSH software package 

  sudo apt-get -y install openssh-server

2)To enable SSH

  sudo systemctl enable ssh

3)if required change the configurations from the sshd config file

 

  sudo systemctl start ssh

 

  sudo systemctl status ssh

 

  sudo ssh localhost

 

Then enter your root or user password 
